    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://losangeles.craigslist.org/lac/ret/6036253770.html"></div>
        </div>
If you love fabric and sewing, are good with people and customer service and have experience in retail, then we have a job for you. We are a growing fabric wholesaler in the Los Angeles area and have recently opened a fabric retail store adjacent to our warehouse and are in need of a responsible individual to help run the store. We sell an assortment of flat fold fabrics at great, discounted prices. Our store location is not in the fashion district but we are close and want to market our store to that larger customer base.<br>
<br>
Daily responsibilities: <br>
â  Open and set up the store.<br>
â  Maintain and organize the store by merchandising and keeping the store looking as attractive as possible.<br>
â  Assist customers with purchases and answer any fabric-related questions.<br>
â  Attend to social media accounts, i.e.: Facebook and Instagram. It is crucial that we market the store on social media, and proper and effective content is key. Answer all inquiries that come in through social media. <br>
â  Develop effective marketing strategies for the shop.<br>
â  Maintain fabric quantities and replenish with new fabrics as necessary. All of the fabric sold in the retail shop comes from our warehouse and communication is very important in order to keep the shop updated with new fabric.<br>
<br>
Qualifications:<br>
â  Minimum 1 year experience within a retail setting, management preferred.<br>
â  Basic Office programs including Word and Excel.<br>
â  Some photo editing skills.<br>
â  Excellent written and communication skills.<br>
â  An eye for merchandising and styling both images and actual store.<br>
â  MUST have Knowledge of Textiles and/or Fashion.<br>
â  Bilingual: fluent in both English and Spanish.<br>
<br>
<br>
We are really excited to grow our retail store and need the right person to help take our business to the next level.<br>
<br>
Compensation: $12.00 hourly PLUS A MONTHLY INCREMENTAL TIERED BONUS BASED ON SALES VOLUME with room for pay increase with sales-driven results.<br>
<br>
If you feel that this is the job for you, please send resume with a quick intro about yourself in the body of the email.  When you send your resume, it MUST detail your fabric knowledge and why you think this job pertains to you.    </section>

